- "blossoms" metaphorically refers to products;
- "gathered the most sunlight" metaphorically refers to products with the highest total revenue;
- "lens of customer feedback" refers to the average rating of the products.

- "Top performers" refers to products with the highest total revenue;
- "Customer satisfaction" is measured by the average rating of the product;
- The query limits the results to the top 5 products;
- The products are first ordered by total revenue, and then by average rating if the revenue is the same.

- 'Blossomed into stars' refers to products that have performed exceptionally well in terms of revenue and customer satisfaction;
- 'Generating over $10,000 in revenue' means the total revenue from sales for the product exceeds $10,000;
- 'Earning an average feedback rating of more than 4' means the average feedback rating for the product is greater than 4 out of 5.

- 'shining bright' refers to generating high revenue;
- 'top 3 best-selling products' refers to the products with the highest revenue in the last 30 days;
- 'past month' refers to the last 30 days.

- "blossomed into stars" refers to products and stores that have performed exceptionally well;
- "dawn of 2020 and the close of 2022" refers to the date range from January 1, 2020, to December 31, 2022;
- "brightness of their total revenue" refers to the total revenue generated, with the highest revenue appearing first.

- "species" refers to `product_name`;
- "brand" refers to `brand_name`;
- "size" refers to the physical size of the product;
- "package type" refers to the type of packaging;
- "most abundant" means ordered by the highest count of `product_id`.
